<subSubSection id="C37565586437FF9FFF1AF3AD48ACC1C6" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD036D36437FF9FFF1AF3AD48CBC051" blockId="7.[189,441,1513,1540]" box="[189,441,1513,1540]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<heading id="D09881BF6437FF9FFF1AF3AD48CBC051" bold="true" box="[189,441,1513,1540]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B91BEAC16437FF9FFF1AF3AD48CBC051" bold="true" box="[189,441,1513,1540]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Preliminary remark</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD036D36437FF9FFF1AF05C48ACC1C6" blockId="7.[189,1401,1560,1939]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
The original diagnosis of 
<emphasis id="B91BEAC16437FF9FFDA3F05C4BEEC067" box="[516,668,1560,1586]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Clavofabella</emphasis>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE4B226437FF9FFD73F05C4AC6C066" author="Martinsson A." box="[724,948,1560,1587]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 31" refId="ref30971" refString="Martinsson A. 1955. Studies on the ostracode family Primitiopsidae. Bulletin of the Geological Institution of Uppsala 36 (1): 1 - 31." type="journal article" year="1955">Martinsson (1955)</bibRefCitation>
is questionable because it does not include characters shared by all specimens: “Dolonate flanges do not meet posteriorly. Dolon that continues forwards in a velar ridge or a velar bend” (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE4B226437FF9FFC8CF01A4D56C02C" author="Martinsson A." box="[811,1060,1630,1657]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 31" refId="ref30971" refString="Martinsson A. 1955. Studies on the ostracode family Primitiopsidae. Bulletin of the Geological Institution of Uppsala 36 (1): 1 - 31." type="journal article" year="1955">Martinsson 1955: 23</bibRefCitation>
). These structures are absent in non-dolonate specimens described or mentioned by Martinsson in the same paper in 
<emphasis id="B91BEAC16437FF9FFB78F0C64823C0EA" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Clavofabella multidentata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE4B226437FF9FFEFEF0E14B5BC095" author="Martinsson A." box="[345,553,1701,1728]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 31" refId="ref30971" refString="Martinsson A. 1955. Studies on the ostracode family Primitiopsidae. Bulletin of the Geological Institution of Uppsala 36 (1): 1 - 31." type="journal article" year="1955">Martinsson, 1955</bibRefCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="B91BEAC16437FF9FFD90F0E14A34C0EA" box="[567,838,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Clavofabella incurvata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE4B226437FF9FFCE9F0E14D6EC095" author="Martinsson A." box="[846,1052,1701,1728]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 31" refId="ref30971" refString="Martinsson A. 1955. Studies on the ostracode family Primitiopsidae. Bulletin of the Geological Institution of Uppsala 36 (1): 1 - 31." type="journal article" year="1955">Martinsson, 1955</bibRefCitation>
and 
<emphasis id="B91BEAC16437FF9FFBF1F0E14C05C0EA" box="[1110,1399,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Clavofabella reticristata</emphasis>
(Jones, 1888). We follow the diagnosis of 
<emphasis id="B91BEAC16437FF9FFD1EF08C4A23C0B7" box="[697,849,1736,1762]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Clavofabella</emphasis>
provided in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE4B226437FF9FFC4EF08D4DFDC0B6" author="Moore R. C." box="[1001,1167,1736,1763]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref31105" refString="Moore R. C. 1961. Treatise on Invertebrate Paleontology. Arthropoda 3, Crustacea, Ostracoda. Geological Society of America and University of Kansas Press." type="book" year="1961">Moore (1961)</bibRefCitation>
because it is based on characters shared by all forms: “inequivalved, 
<collectionCode id="ED7EAE166437FF9FFC8DF0A84A22C153" box="[810,848,1772,1798]" country="Italy" name="Collection of Leptospira Strains" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">RV</collectionCode>
overlapping LV; hinge consisting of median groove with corresponding ridge and lateral elongate pits and sockets; unisulcate […]; surface pitted or reticulate, marginal structure tuberculate” (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE4B226437FF9FFD47F1764AC4C119" author="Moore R. C." box="[736,950,1841,1868]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref31105" refString="Moore R. C. 1961. Treatise on Invertebrate Paleontology. Arthropoda 3, Crustacea, Ostracoda. Geological Society of America and University of Kansas Press." type="book" year="1961">Moore 1961: 174</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE4B226437FF9FFC6BF1764D00C119" author="Moore R. C." box="[972,1138,1841,1868]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref31105" refString="Moore R. C. 1961. Treatise on Invertebrate Paleontology. Arthropoda 3, Crustacea, Ostracoda. Geological Society of America and University of Kansas Press." type="book" year="1961">Moore (1961)</bibRefCitation>
furthermore indicates that velar structures are developed as ridge but that in heteromorphs they are wider and form posterior flanges that do not meet.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
